Lauren Branning tried to put the spice back in her relationship with boyfriend Steven Beale on EastEnders last night. 
Actress Jacqueline Jossa appeared in black lacy lingerie and stockings as she tried to seduce Steven. 
She came downstairs in a silk dressing gown which she opened to reveal her underwear. 
"I thought we can spice things up a bit," Lauren said as she jumped on his lap. Lauren Branning decided to spice things up in her relationship (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) She stripped down to her lingerie (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) 
She hand fed him a spicy guacamole dip and crisps â€“ but things got awkward when the food was too hot for him. 
And as Lauren dived for his trousers, he resisted his girlfriend's advances. She tried to seduce her boyfriend Steven Beale (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) He wasn't impressed (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) 
"Hang on, you did wash your hands right?" he said, thinking of the chillies she'd just handled. 
"Of course I have," she insisted. Things got awkward (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) Lauren's romantic dreams were dashed (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) 
But it was too late, the moment was gone and Lauren jumped up when Jane Fowler came through the door.
